text: Lithocarpus indutus is a species of plant in the family Fagaceae. Some common names it goes by are bataruwa, pasang bodas, and pasang balung. It is a tree endemic to Java in Indonesia. It is a vulnerable species threatened by habitat loss. ==References== indutus Category:Endemic flora of Java Category:Vulnerable plants Category:Taxonomy articles created by Polbot
